# ============================================================
# Globe AMS — 01. Admin Authentication
# ============================================================
# Seeded admin: admin@globe.com / Admin@123!
# Tenant slug:  globe  (role: TenantAdmin — NOT SuperAdmin)
#
# ⚠ The seeded admin has TenantAdmin role, not SuperAdmin.
#   To create new tenants you need SuperAdmin.
#   See 02_tenant-management.http for setup instructions.
#
# Run order: send these requests top to bottom.
# Copy accessToken + tenantId from the login response for use in later files.
# ============================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5006

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 1. Login as seeded Globe TenantAdmin (HAPPY PATH)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# @name adminLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@globe.com",
  "password": "Admin@123!",
  "tenantSlug": "globe"
}

###
# ✅ Expected 200:
# {
#   "accessToken": "<jwt>",    ← copy to @globeAdminToken in later files
#   "refreshToken": "<token>", ← copy to @globeRefreshToken
#   "expiresAt": "...",
#   "userId": "<guid>",
#   "email": "admin@globe.com",
#   "fullName": "Admin User",
#   "role": "TenantAdmin",
#   "tenantId": "<globe-guid>" ← copy to @globeTenantId in later files
# }
# Decode at https://jwt.io to verify claims include "tenantId" and "role".

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 2. Login with wrong password (expect 400)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@globe.com",
  "password": "WrongPassword!",
  "tenantSlug": "globe"
}

###
# ❌ Expected 400 Bad Request — "Invalid credentials."

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 3. Login with non-existent tenant slug (expect 404)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# MULTI-TENANCY: correct credentials + wrong slug → tenant not found
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@globe.com",
  "password": "Admin@123!",
  "tenantSlug": "nonexistent-tenant"
}

###
# ❌ Expected 404 Not Found
# Tenant resolution happens before credential check.
# Slug "nonexistent-tenant" has no Tenant row → NotFoundException.

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 4. Login with user from another tenant using Globe slug (expect 403)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# MULTI-TENANCY: a user registered in alpha-clinic cannot login via globe slug.
# Uncomment after registering alice@alphaclinic.com in alpha-clinic tenant.
#
# POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
# Content-Type: application/json
#
# {
#   "email": "alice@alphaclinic.com",
#   "password": "Alpha@123!",
#   "tenantSlug": "globe"
# }
#
# ❌ Expected 403 Forbidden — "User does not belong to this tenant."
# Alice's AppUser.TenantId = alpha-clinic, so globe login is rejected.

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 5. Login with empty body (expect 400 / validation error)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###
# ❌ Expected 400 Bad Request — FluentValidation errors for required fields
